HEADWORD: Orally
<hw>O"ral*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In an oral
manner.</def> <rj><au>Tillotson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>By, with, or in, the mouth; <as>as, to receive the
sacrament <ex>orally</ex></as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Usher.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>oral surgery</ent>⟦br⟧
